        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-24T21:25:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I am, however, very slightly worried that this expression will evaluate to 0. I’d feel better with a saturated_cast\u003cValueSizeType\u003e(n + 1), with the 1 on the inside, on the assumption that it’s a lot harder to exhaust a size_t than a uint32_t, which is what ValueSizeType is now.\n\n(I’m also thinking about it from the perspective that ValueSizeType might as well be a uint16_t while kValueMaxSize is 2048. We wouldn’t actually want to do that because it restricts how large kValueMaxSize could be raised given the wire format, but I’m just giving you my mental context here. In any event, doing the addition on the maybe-wider size_t and choosing saturation rather than truncation seems appropriate in any context.)",
